            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The \"memory leak\" also happens with normal logging; the debug log level is not needed (but of course adds overhead). This example is an extreme case but this also happens (with smaller increments) on normal projects. It also doesn't sound like this is a bad or off-spec server implementation, so this is something we should guard against in general. \n\nI'll report it to the server, too, though; some debouncing on their side (or more parsimonious updates) can't hurt.",
